###How to fix the App Dependencies issue of ssri:7.1.0 of pkg:npm/ssri@7.1.0 in nginx web server and which owasp top 10 web 2021 category this issue belong to ?
The App Dependencies issue of ssri:7.1.0 of pkg:npm/ssri@7.1.0 in nginx web server can be fixed by upgrading to a newer version of ssri. ssri has a known vulnerability that can be exploited to allow attackers to execute arbitrary code on the target system. This vulnerability is tracked as CVE-2022-37149.

To upgrade ssri, you can run the following command:

```
npm install ssri@latest
```

Once ssri has been upgraded, you need to restart your nginx web server.

This issue belongs to the OWASP Top 10 Web 2021 category of **A1: Injection**. Injection flaws occur when an attacker can inject malicious code into a web application. This can allow the attacker to take control of the application, steal data, or even execute arbitrary code on the target system.

To protect against injection flaws, you should always validate user input before using it in your application. You should also use prepared statements when querying databases.

Here are some additional tips for preventing injection flaws:

* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to filter malicious traffic.
* Keep your web application software up to date.
* Train your developers on how to prevent injection flaws.

By following these tips, you can help to protect your web application from injection flaws and other security vulnerabilities.
